The call CHORAL (Cultural Heritage Outreach in RomAnce Languages), for full=
y-funded three-year doctoral programmes between UNITA Alliance universities=
 with joint supervision, is open until 15 January 2025.

The call offers 14 scholarships on 25 PhD research topics in 7 UNITA Allian=
ce universities, which will confer a double degree and require internationa=
l mobility.

Why undertake a CORAL PhD?

Obtain high-quality training and research guaranteed by the expertise of th=
e UNITA Alliance research laboratories within the Hub dedicated to cultural=
 heritage.
Collaborate with international partners and leaders in the cultural heritag=
e sector.
Enjoy dedicated support: from reception to professional integration.
Be protagonists in the social, economic and cultural transformation of cros=
s-border rural and mountain territories.
Benefit from dedicated mobility and travel allowances and support for resea=
rch expenses.
Graduate with a double degree from 2 different European universities.
All information and the link to apply on the dedicated website.

For further information, please contact the support office at choral@univ-p=
